<HEAD>Rare Snow Leopard Makes Neighbors Nervous</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOUGHTON, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The neighbors are worried about a 110-pound pet snow leopard caged in his owner's suburban yard, but officials say the owner is within his rights. <PERSON> Albert </PERSON> <PERSON> Porges </PERSON> bought the big cat, member of an endangered species in the <LOCATION> Himalayas </LOCATION>, at auction last year and says there is no town bylaw preventing him from having the animal as long as he meets strict state and federal rules. `` It's an issue everyone in the neighborhood is upset about,'' said <PERSON> Margaret </PERSON> <PERSON> Conopka </PERSON>, who lives nearby with her husband and three young children. Town animal control officer <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Doten </PERSON> said he has visited the leopard's home, a 36-by-12-foot cage that is 20 feet high. `` It's satisfactory to me, but if it ever got loose, I do n't know what we would do about it,'' he said
