<HEAD>British Inflation Rate Fell To 20-Year Low</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Inflation in <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> fell to an annual rate of 3.3 percent in 1987, its lowest level in 20 years, the government said. Consumer prices rose 3.3 percent during the year, down from 3.9 percent in 1986 and the lowest level since 1967, the <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Employment </ORGANIZATION> said Wednesday. The price of some goods fell. Coffee dropped 8 percent and gas charges were 4.5 percent lower, but that was offset in part by a 22 percent rise in vehicle insurance costs.
