<TEXT>
 High-ranking officials of <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Bulgaria </LOCATION>, long regarded among <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION>'s staunchest allies, have dates in the coming weeks with Secretary of State <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON>. They are <PERSON> Herman </PERSON> <PERSON> Axen </PERSON>, a member of <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION>'s ruling politburo, and <PERSON> Andrei </PERSON> <PERSON> Lukanov </PERSON>, Bulgarian minister of foreign economic relations and alternate politburo member. Both are described by <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> officials as the highest-ranking members of their respective communist hierarchies ever to visit <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> and East German sources, speaking on condition of anonymity, said a May 3 meeting between <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> and <PERSON> Axen </PERSON> was arranged after the East German leader was invited to speak May 4 at the <ORGANIZATION> Johns </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hopkins </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Contemporary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> German </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Studies </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Axen </PERSON> holds no office in the East German government, but is the top international affairs officer of the <ORGANIZATION> Socialist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Unity </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>, the official name of the governing communist organization. <PERSON> Lukanov </PERSON> is scheduled to meet <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> during an April 25-26 visit to <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, followed by a coast-to-coast trade promotion tour with a high-level delegation. Noted as an economic reformer, <PERSON> Lukanov </PERSON> will be the first senior Bulgarian cabinet minister in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION