<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Stock prices reached an all-time high today in <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> following the overnight advance on Wall Street, while the dollar also edged up against the Japanese yen. On the <ORGANIZATION> Tokyo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Nikkei </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Average </ORGANIZATION> of 225 selected issues, which gained 195.82 points Wednesday, gained another 265.02 points, or 0.99 percent, closing the day at 26,767.19. The dollar closed at 125.70 yen, the day's high, up 0.67 yen from its close Wednesday of 125.03 yen. It had opened the day at 125.60 yen and traded between 125.40-125 .70 yen `` The overnight advance on Wall Street and the stronger dollar boosted the stock average,'' said <PERSON> Tadaaki </PERSON> <PERSON> Uehara </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Wako </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <PERSON> Taeko </PERSON> <PERSON> Kobayashi </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tokyo </ORGANIZATION> said the foreign exchange market, `` which started volatile in the morning following the overnight surge on Wall Street, now seems stable without anything particular directing participants.'' In <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> on Wednesday, the <ORGANIZATION> Dow </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jones </ORGANIZATION> industrial average closed at 2,061.67, up 64.16 points over Tuesday's close.
