<HEAD>90-Year-Old Wins Sixth Four-Year Term On Town Council</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BAY HARBOR ISLANDS, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A 90-year-old man who is <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>'s oldest elected official as well as one of the oldest in the nation has won his sixth four-year seat on the town council. <PERSON> Louis </PERSON> <PERSON> Haas </PERSON>, a retired obstetrician, joined the council in 1968, 11 years after moving to <LOCATION> Bay </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Harbor </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Islands </LOCATION>. He's the oldest elected official known to the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> League </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cities </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Retired </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Persons </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>. `` And if I live another four years, I surely will be -LRB- the oldest -RRB-,'' <PERSON> Haas </PERSON> said after his victory Tuesday. <PERSON> Haas </PERSON> works at his $ 1-a-year post from 6 a.m., when he begins reading, chatting with residents and signing city checks. Sometime before noon he rides through town with the police chief on what <PERSON> Haas </PERSON> calls `` inspection.'' Afternoons are spent reading and resting for night meetings. <PERSON> Haas </PERSON> counts <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Rep. <PERSON> Claude </PERSON> <PERSON> Pepper </PERSON>, the 87-year-old <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION> Democrat and oldest member of <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>, among his friends. `` We often compare notes about this century with the last,'' <PERSON> Pepper </PERSON> said. `` We look forward to comparing the next century with this.'' A member of <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION>'s class of 1918, <PERSON> Haas </PERSON> has lived alone since his second wife, <PERSON> Ceil </PERSON>, died in 1981. His first wife, <PERSON> Sydelle </PERSON>, died in 1949.
