<HEAD>U.S. Doctors Fear Tear Gas Could Cause Deaths in Israel</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Israel Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOAN MOWER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Two doctors say U.S.-made tear gas used by <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> to curb <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> protests may be causing deaths and injuries to civilians, but further studies are needed to determine the extent of the problem. `` Adequate research just has not been done,'' said Dr. <PERSON> Howard </PERSON> <PERSON> Hu </PERSON>, an epidemiologist at the <ORGANIZATION> Harvard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Health </ORGANIZATION>. Hu and Dr. <PERSON> Jonathan </PERSON> <PERSON> Fine </PERSON> are associated with <ORGANIZATION> Physicians </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Human </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rights </ORGANIZATION>, a Boston-based group which is concerned that the Israelis may be misusing tear gas, a chemical agent that overcomes its victims by causing severe irritation to the eyes, skin and respiratory tract. If tear gas is handled properly, the effects are not long-lasting, but it can kill people if it is fired in high doses into enclosed areas. `` It would not surprise me if there were deaths of infants or the infirm'' from too much exposure to tear gas in <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Fine </PERSON> said. `` We believe it is important to do planned studies on this.'' The <ORGANIZATION> American-Arab </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Anti-Discrimination </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, a lobbying group, claims that more than 30 people have died in <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> and in the Israeli-occupied <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> from exposure to tear gas, which also has caused injuries and miscarriages. <PERSON> Yossi </PERSON> <PERSON> Gal </PERSON>, a spokesman at the Israeli Embassy, said those figures are wildly inflated. The Israelis