<HEAD>Prize Awarded to AIDS, Smallpox Researchers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> and a Frenchman whose independent studies led to the discovery of the AIDS virus shared the <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> Prize in preventive medicine Thursday. The Science and <ORGANIZATION> Technology </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Japan </ORGANIZATION> awarded another prize in the same category to <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION>, Japanese and Australian scientists credited with eradicating smallpox from the earth. French scientist <PERSON> Georges </PERSON> <PERSON> Vendryes </PERSON>, who pioneered development of the fast-breeder type nuclear reactor, won the <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> Prize for energy technology. <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Gallo </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institutes </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Health </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Luc </PERSON> <PERSON> Montagnier </PERSON> of <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>'s Pasteur institute shared a $ 200,000 prize for their work on AIDS. Working separately, <PERSON> Gallo </PERSON> and <PERSON> Montagnier </PERSON> both discovered the deadly virus and helped develop blood tests to detect infection. `` There would be no mistake in thinking that the methodology has been established by the two doctors for the control of an infectious disease which has become a major problem of the 20th Century,'' the prize committee said. `` In parts of the world -LRB- AIDS -RRB- is akin to genocide,'' <PERSON> Gallo </PERSON> said in accepting the prize at the National Theater. `` It is global, and mostly, it destroys the young.'' <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Henderson </PERSON> of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Isao </PERSON> <PERSON> Arita </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> and <PERSON> Frank </PER