LOCATION>, the head of a `` parallel power that has enabled us to tie the hands of the -LRB- <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> -RRB- administration.'' <PERSON> Ortega </PERSON> said Thursday his government sent a letter of protest to the <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> States </ORGANIZATION> denouncing a reported offer by <LOCATION> Honduras </LOCATION> to allow Contra supplies from the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> to arrive there. Speaking in a radio interview, <PERSON> Ortega </PERSON> said <LOCATION> Honduras </LOCATION> made itself an `` instrument of American policies'' by acting as an `` illegal springboard for supplies for the mercenary forces.''
