f the assailants or victims. They said no <ORGANIZATION> Red </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cross </ORGANIZATION> personnel were hurt. The attack by Amal on <LOCATION> Ghaziyeh </LOCATION> `` obviously aims at stripping <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION> in south <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> of its main supply line,'' said the police spokesman, who can not be named in line with standing regulations. The road to south <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> has been blocked at <LOCATION> Ghaziyeh </LOCATION> since Wednesday, when <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION> fighters overran an Amal checkpoint in the town. The spokesman said <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION>'s 40 fighters in the village of <LOCATION> Kfar </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Roumman </LOCATION> surrendered to Amal a few hours after <ORGANIZATION> Amal </ORGANIZATION> seized the adjacent town of <LOCATION> Nabatiyeh </LOCATION> in a `` sweeping attack.'' <LOCATION> Nabatiyeh </LOCATION>, 18 miles southeast of <LOCATION> Sidon </LOCATION>, is a mainly Shiite town of 50,000. An <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> reporter saw six <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION> fighters, their hands up, emerging from a gutted house in <LOCATION> Nabatiyeh </LOCATION>'s old sector and surrendering to Amal militiamen. Fighting for <LOCATION> Nabatiyeh </LOCATION> was fierce. The two sides traded rocket-propelled grenades and mortar rounds until <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION>'s last stronghold at the town's <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> school fell to Aamal attackers. The school, occupied by <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION> when the confrontation broke out Tuesday, was devastated with its walls peppered with shell holes, blown-out windows and fire-blackened wooden desks.
