tep and to help the starving people in any way possible.'' It said the order was intended `` to starve the people of <LOCATION> Eritrea </LOCATION> and <PERSON> Tigre </PERSON> and cow them into submission. `` For this purpose, the dergue intends to put the charitable organizations' food, vehicles and other services to military use.'' Eritrean rebels have been fighting for 27 years against the central government in <LOCATION> Ethiopia </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>'s longest civil war. In neighboring Tigre, another separatist group, the <ORGANIZATION> Tigre </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION>, has been fighting for 14 years. The hostilities have disrupted relief efforts in both regions, where crop failures threaten 3.5 million people with starvation. Overall, nearly 7 million Ethiopians face famine without outside help. About 60 non-governmental relief organizations operate in <LOCATION> Ethiopia </LOCATION>, but only a few operate in <LOCATION> Eritrea </LOCATION> and Tigre.
