 Educator <PERSON> Ramona </PERSON> <PERSON> Hoage </PERSON> <PERSON> Edelin </PERSON> was named acting chief executive officer of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Urban </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Coalition </ORGANIZATION> on Thursday. `` I am confident that ... she will provide the coalition with strong, effective, creative leadership as the organization moves to better serve its constituences in the 1990s and beyond,'' said coalition president <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Carl </PERSON> <PERSON> Holman </PERSON>. <PERSON> Edelin </PERSON>, a senior staff member of the coalition for 11 years, is a Phi Beta Kappa graduate of <ORGANIZATION> Fisk </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> and holds a Ph.D. in philosophy from <ORGANIZATION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION>. She is the co-developer and executive director of `` Say YES to a Youngster's Future,'' the organization's education program to prepare low-income, minority children and females for the high-tech careers and lifestyles of the future. Since its founding in 1967, the coalition has specialized in building corporate-government-community partnerships to upgrade the education, health care, housing and economy of the nation's urban areas.
