 The chants of women recruits jogging in the warm April sun drift through the open windows of the Law Center at the <ORGANIZATION> Marine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corps </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Recruit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Depot </ORGANIZATION>. Inside, <ORGANIZATION> Marine </ORGANIZATION> officers are continuing an investigation of lesbianism, which has already led to charges against several former drill instructors and at least one officer. Five women <ORGANIZATION> Marines </ORGANIZATION> have been charged with various counts including committing indecent acts. Two other women who were due to go before administrative hearing boards are seeking discharges.
