 <ORGANIZATION> Intel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, the surging semiconductor manufacturer, said Thursday its profit more than tripled in its latest fiscal quarter. <ORGANIZATION> Intel </ORGANIZATION> said it earned $ 94 million, or 54 cents a share, in the three months ended March 26, up from $ 26 million, or 14 cents a share, in the year-earlier quarter. Revenue rose 61 percent to a record $ 636 million from $ 395 million. `` We are experiencing strong demand for microprocessors, microcontrollers, memories, peripheral components and personal computer platforms,'' <PERSON> Andrew </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Grove </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Intel </ORGANIZATION>'s president, said in a news release.
