<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> WINSTON-SALEM </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.C. </LOCATION> -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> -RRB- _ <ORGANIZATION> Piedmont </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> announced price reductions Thursday on nonrefundable fares for tickets purchased by April 17, joining two other airlines which cut prices earlier this week. None of the fares exceed $ 198 roundtrip, including those for transcontinental travel, and they apply to <LOCATION> Piedmont </LOCATION> flights between noon on Mondays and noon on Thursdays throughout the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> route system. The fares are available for flights scheduled between April 18 and June 15. `` The timing of this sale is perfect for parents hoping to attend their children's graduation ceremonies at distant colleges and universities, for couples planning budget honeymoons to extend their travel range to include a <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> resort, and for kids to get an extra visit from their grandparents,'' said <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Daniel </PERSON> <PERSON> Brock </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Piedmont </LOCATION>'s senior vice president of marketing. Once tickets are purchased, plans can not be changed. The fares may not apply to some routes served by <LOCATION> Piedmont </LOCATION> regional and commuter airline partners. The price reduction comes two days after <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>, the nation's sixth-largest and fifth-ranked airlines, respectively, said they were cutting some fares in anticipation of a slack period coming up for leisure travel. Although there are some minor differences, <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> introduced similar programs. The non-refundable tickets must be purchased by April 14 -LRB- starting Tuesday for <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> and Wednesday for <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> -RRB-, and used for travel from April 18 through June 15. Passengers must travel between noon Monday and noon Thursday. Round-trip travel and a Saturday night stay are required. Those restrictions limit the program to eight travel days in April, 18 days in May and nine in June.
